        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix targeting RX contexts",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix targeting RX contexts\n\nPrior to this commit, only RX context 0 would be targeted by untagged\nmessages. Untagged messages are used for sending the LNet payload for\nan immediate transaction and the bulk request message for a bulk\ntransaction. The kfi header for these messages contains a prefer_rx\nfield. The prefer_rx field tells the remote target which RX context it\nshould use when sending untagged messages to the local peer. While the\nprefer_rx field was being processed and the peer structure rx_context\nfield being updated accordingly, the rx_context  was never used to\nconstruct a kfi address (kfi_addr_t) to target a specific RX context.\nThis patch fixes this by using kfilnd_peer_get_kfi_addr() to generate\na kfi address which targets a specific RX context.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-10133\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I4a6cccadf09f626b44ce76c18f0f39c0db9570ad\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
